Scheme. 1, whose foolish philosophy made me an infrequent wor- shipper of the gods, am now obliged to change my opinions. For 1 heard Jupiter thunder from a clear sky with such a clap that all the world was shaken. The gods, Ι confess it now, do interfere in the affairs of men, to exalt the lowly and bring down the proud.
